<usermanual>
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

									BEHAVIOURAL ASSESSMENT SCALE (BAS)
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

Script Author: Katja Borchert, Ph.D. (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC
Date: 06-30-2014
last updated:  02-17-2022 by K. Borchert (katjab@millisecond.com) for Millisecond Software, LLC

Script Copyright © 02-17-2022 Millisecond Software

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
BACKGROUND INFO 	
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
This script implements the Behavioural Assessment Scale as described in:

Ritchie, K. & Ledesert, B. (1991). The Measurement of Incapacity in the Severly Demented Elderly: The
Validation of a Behavioural Assessment Scale. International Journal of Geriatric Psychiatry, 6, 217-226.

The Behavioural Assessment Scale assesses the intellectual functioning and adaptive behaviors in 
patients suffering from severe dementia.

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
OVERVIEW
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	

the script presents 11 surveypages that cover the 5 subcategories 
(Language - 5 questions, 
Social Integration - 5 questions, 
Occupation & Orientation - 3 questions, 
Physical Independence - 16 questions, 
Mobility - 3 questions) described by Ritchie & Ledesert (1991)

A total score (expressions.BAS_score) is calculated at the end.


___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DURATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
the default set-up of the script takes appr. 5 minutes to complete

___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
DATA FILE INFORMATION 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________
The default data stored in the data files are:

(1) Raw data file: 'bas.iqdat'

date, time:						date and time script was run with the current group/subjectnumber 
subject, group, session:	  	with the current subject/groupnumber/session id
build:							the Inquisit build 

q*_response:					response given (in assigned values)
								- see individual questions under section QUESTIONS for assigned values (/optionvalues = )
q*_latency:						how much time in ms the participant spent on the surveypage with this particular question (the last time this particular surveypage was visited)

(2) Summary data file: 'bas_summary*.iqdat'

inquisit.version:				Inquisit version run
computer.platform:				the platform the script was run on (win/mac/ios/android)
startDate:						date script was run
startTime:						time script was started
subjectid:						assigned subject id number
groupid:						assigned group id number
sessionid:						assigned session id number
elapsedTime:					time it took to run script (in ms); measured from onset to offset of script
completed:						0 = script was not completed (prematurely aborted); 
								1 = script was completed (all conditions run)
								
checkboxscore:				stores the scoresum of all items presented as checkboxes
radiobuttonscore:			calculates subtotal scoresum from all radiobutton items
BAS_score:					calculates the totalscore based on all items


___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
EDITABLE CODE 
___________________________________________________________________________________________________________________	
check below for (relatively) easily editable parameters, stimuli, instructions etc. 
Keep in mind that you can use this script as a template and therefore always "mess" with the entire code 
to further customize your experiment.

The parameters you can change are:

/pageinstructions:			the instructions that appear at the top of each surveypage


</usermanual>


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	EDITABLE PARAMETERS: change editable parameters here
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************

<parameters>
/pageinstructions = "Please select the answers that apply best."
</parameters>



**************************************************************************************************************
								!!!REMAINING CODE: Customize after careful consideration only!!!
**************************************************************************************************************


**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
	DEFAULTS
**************************************************************************************************************
**************************************************************************************************************
script requires Inquisit 6.5.2.0 or higher

<defaults>
/canvasaspectratio = (4,3)
/minimumversion = "6.5.2.0"
/ fontstyle = ("Arial", 3%, false, false, false, false, 5, 1)
/txbgcolor = white
/ txcolor = black
</defaults>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	DATA: this section contains data file information
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

********************
Summary data
********************

<summarydata>
/ columns = (inquisit.version, computer.platform, script.startDate, script.startTime, script.subjectId, script.groupId, script.sessionId, 
script.elapsedTime, script.completed, 
values.checkboxscore, expressions.radiobuttonscore, expressions.BAS_score)
</summarydata>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	VALUES/EXPRESSIONS: automatically updated
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
/checkboxscore:					stores the scoresum of all items presented as checkboxes

<values>
/checkboxscore = 0
</values>

/radiobuttonscore:				calculates subtotal scoresum from radiobutton items
/calculatecheckboxscore:		calculates the scoresum of all items presented as checkboxes
/BAS_total:						calculates the totalscore based on all items

<expressions>
/radiobuttonscore = radiobuttons.activities.response + radiobuttons.bathing.response + radiobuttons.contactwithothers.response +
radiobuttons.cooperativeness.response + radiobuttons.dentalhygiene.response + radiobuttons.dressing.response + radiobuttons.drinking.response + 
radiobuttons.fecalcontinence.response + radiobuttons.goingtobed.response + radiobuttons.oralcomprehension.response + 
radiobuttons.oralexpression.response + radiobuttons.orientation.response + radiobuttons.puttingonshoes.response + radiobuttons.recogwrittenlanguage.response + 
radiobuttons.shaving.response + radiobuttons.sleep.response + radiobuttons.takingoffshoes.response + radiobuttons.telephone.response +
radiobuttons.undressing.response + radiobuttons.urinarycontinence.response + radiobuttons.utensils.response + radiobuttons.walking.response + 
radiobuttons.writingability.response

/calculatecheckboxscore =
if (checkboxes.fampersonawareness.selected.1) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.fampersonawareness.selected.2) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.fampersonawareness.selected.3) values.checkboxscore += 1;

if (checkboxes.handcontrol.selected.1) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.handcontrol.selected.2) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.handcontrol.selected.3) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.handcontrol.selected.4) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.handcontrol.selected.5) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.handcontrol.selected.6) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.handcontrol.selected.7) values.checkboxscore += 1;

if (checkboxes.nonverbalexpression.selected.1) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.nonverbalexpression.selected.2) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.nonverbalexpression.selected.3) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.nonverbalexpression.selected.4) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.nonverbalexpression.selected.5) values.checkboxscore += 1;

if (!checkboxes.postureandgait.selected.1) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (!checkboxes.postureandgait.selected.2) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (!checkboxes.postureandgait.selected.3) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (!checkboxes.postureandgait.selected.4) values.checkboxscore += 1;

if (!checkboxes.problem_daytime_behavior.selected.1) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (!checkboxes.problem_daytime_behavior.selected.2) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (!checkboxes.problem_daytime_behavior.selected.3) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (!checkboxes.problem_daytime_behavior.selected.4) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (!checkboxes.problem_daytime_behavior.selected.5) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (!checkboxes.problem_daytime_behavior.selected.6) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (!checkboxes.problem_daytime_behavior.selected.7) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (!checkboxes.problem_daytime_behavior.selected.8) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (!checkboxes.problem_daytime_behavior.selected.9) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (!checkboxes.problem_daytime_behavior.selected.10) values.checkboxscore += 1;

if (!checkboxes.problem_nighttime_behavior.selected.1) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (!checkboxes.problem_nighttime_behavior.selected.2) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (!checkboxes.problem_nighttime_behavior.selected.3) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (!checkboxes.problem_nighttime_behavior.selected.4) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (!checkboxes.problem_nighttime_behavior.selected.5) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (!checkboxes.problem_nighttime_behavior.selected.6) values.checkboxscore += 1;

if (checkboxes.tasks.selected.1) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.tasks.selected.2) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.tasks.selected.3) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.tasks.selected.4) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.tasks.selected.5) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.tasks.selected.6) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.tasks.selected.7) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.tasks.selected.8) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.tasks.selected.9) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.tasks.selected.10) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.tasks.selected.11) values.checkboxscore += 1;

if (checkboxes.useoftoilet.selected.1) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.useoftoilet.selected.2) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.useoftoilet.selected.3) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.useoftoilet.selected.4) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.useoftoilet.selected.5) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.useoftoilet.selected.6) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.useoftoilet.selected.7) values.checkboxscore += 1;

if (checkboxes.washinghandsandface.selected.1) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.washinghandsandface.selected.2) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.washinghandsandface.selected.3) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.washinghandsandface.selected.4) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.washinghandsandface.selected.5) values.checkboxscore += 1;
if (checkboxes.washinghandsandface.selected.6) values.checkboxscore += 1

/BAS_score = expressions.radiobuttonscore + values.checkboxscore
</expressions>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	QUESTIONS
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
Note: by default all questions are required to be answered. To change
/required = false (editing the setting can throw off the calcuation of the the BAS score)

<radiobuttons oralcomprehension>
/caption = "1. Oral Comprehension"
/ options = ("5 = Understands complex orders (e.g. do this then that)", 
"4 = Mostly replies appropriately to questions",
"3 = Understands simple orders (e.g. sit down)", 
"2 = Reacts when spoken to but often doesn't follow simple orders", 
"1 = Reacts only when spoken to repeatedly",
"0 = No reaction when spoken to")
/ optionvalues = ("5", "4", "3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons oralexpression>
/caption = "2. Oral Expression"
/ options = ("5 = Asks questions", 
"4 = Able to use an appropriate whole sentence",
"3 = Speaks with appropriate words but not sentences", 
"2 = Speaks using words or phrases out of context", 
"1 = Incomprehensible",
"0 = Doesn't speak")
/ optionvalues = ("5", "4", "3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<checkboxes nonverbalexpression>
/ caption="3. Non-verbal expression (score 1 if present)"
/ required = false
/ options=("Nods or smiles to communicate satisfaction", 
"Indicates needs with hands or noises", 
"Laughs",
"Shows anger or happiness without words",
"Communicates an idea with a particular look")
</checkboxes>

<radiobuttons RecogWrittenLanguage>
/caption = "4. Recognition of written language"
/ options = ("6 = Able to read parts of a book or magazine",
"5 = Able to read signs", 
"4 = Recognizes a few words",
"3 = Recognizes own name when written", 
"2 = Looks at pictures in magazine", 
"1 = Looks at pictures in magazines if shown",
"0 = Shows no interest or recognition of pictures")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons WritingAbility>
/caption = "5. Writing Ability"
/ options = (
"4 = Writes short notes or letters",
"3 = Writes several sentences", 
"2 = Writes a single sentence", 
"1 = Writes own name",
"0 = Unable to write at all")
/ optionvalues = ("4", "3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons Cooperativeness>
/caption = "1. Cooperativeness"
/ options = (
"2 = Offers help", 
"1 = Helps only when asked",
"0 = Never helps")
/ optionvalues = ("2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons ContactwithOthers>
/caption = "2. Contact with Others"
/ options = (
"3 = Occasionally initiates contact with others",
"2 = Never initiates contact but replies to others", 
"1 = Watches without becoming involved in others' activities",
"0 = Doesn't seem aware of what others are doing")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<checkboxes FamPersonAwareness>
/ caption="3. Awareness of familiar persons (score 1 if present)"
/ required = false
/ options=(
"Recognizes at least one member of the family", 
"Knows the name of someone close",
"Knows the name of a nurse, doctor or aid")
</checkboxes>

<checkboxes Problem_Daytime_Behavior>
/ caption="4. Problem daytime behavior (score 1 if absent)"
/ required = false
/ options=(
"Demands attention", 
"Swears",
"Vulgar with visitors",
"Obsence behavior",
"Aggressive behavior",
"Disrupts the social life of others",
"Angry outburts",
"Cries out, makes lots of noise",
"Deliberately creates problems between other persons",
"Continually asks questions")
</checkboxes>

<checkboxes Problem_nighttime_Behavior>
/ caption="5. Problem behavior at night (score 1 if absent)"
/ required = false
/ options=(
"Walks around at night", 
"Speaks or mutters at night",
"Cries out for no reason at night",
"Gets dressed at night",
"Spreads feces during the night",
"Sees or hears things that aren't there",
)
</checkboxes>

<radiobuttons Activities>
/caption = "1. Activities"
/ options = (
"4 = Maintains a favorite pastime (e.g. collects coins, paints)",
"3 = Participates in activities if offered",
"2 = Offers help", 
"1 = Helps only when asked",
"0 = Never helps")
/ optionvalues = ("4", "3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<checkboxes Tasks>
/ caption="2. Tasks (score 1 if present)"
/ required = false
/ options=(
"Makes small purchases", 
"Cleans room with help",
"Makes bed with or without help",
"Washes clothes",
"Makes table",
"Clears table",
"Makes tea or coffee",
"Helps with cooking",
"Serves at table",
"Washes up",
"Goes for a walk without getting lost"
)
</checkboxes>

<radiobuttons Orientation>
/caption = "3. Orientation"
/ options = (
"2 = Seeks objects within own room", 
"1 = Visual search of familiar objects",
"0 = Does not seek objects")
/ optionvalues = ("2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons Dressing>
/caption = "1. Dressing"
/ options = (
"5 = Dresses correctly unaided"
"4 = Dresses alone but not correctly",
"3 = Dresses if requested",
"2 = Dresses if requested but needs help", 
"1 = Cooperates when being dressed",
"0 = Uncooperative when being dressed")
/ optionvalues = ("5", "4", "3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons Undressing>
/caption = "2. Undressing"
/ options = (
"4 = Undresses completely without reminder",
"3 = Undresses completely if reminded",
"2 = Undresses with help if reminded", 
"1 = Cooperates ehne being undressed",
"0 = Uncooperative when being undressed")
/ optionvalues = ("4", "3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons PuttingOnShoes>
/caption = "3. Putting on shoes"
/ options = (
"3 = Puts on shoes without help",
"2 = Puts on slippers without help", 
"1 = Puts shoes on but on the wrong foot",
"0 = Has to have shoes put on")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons TakingOffShoes>
/caption = "4. Taking off shoes"
/ options = (
"2 = Takes off shoes", 
"1 = Takes off slippers",
"0 = Needs to have shoes taken off")
/ optionvalues = ("2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons GoingToBed>
/caption = "5. Going to bed"
/ options = (
"2 = Puts self to bed", 
"1 = Put self to bed with some assistance",
"0 = Needs to be put to bed")
/ optionvalues = ("2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons Sleep>
/caption = "6. Sleep"
/ options = (
"3 = Sleeps or rests quietly for at least 6 hours per night",
"2 = Sleeps or rests calmly for 2-6 hours", 
"1 = Reless agitated sleep",
"0 = Sleeps less than two hours per night")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons Telephone>
/caption = "7. Use of telephone"
/ options = (
"3 = Able to telephone alone if given number",
"2 = Able to telephone with help if given number", 
"1 = Picks up reciever and speaks when telephone rings",
"0 = Unable to use telephone")
/ optionvalues = ("3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>


<radiobuttons Utensils>
/caption = "8. Use of eating utensils"
/ options = (
"8 = Able to use knife and fork correctly without spilling food",
"7 = Can eat with spoon and fork correctly without spilling food",
"6 = Eats with spoon and fork but spills a lot",
"5 = Eats only with spoon",
"4 = Eats with spoon but spills a lot",
"3 = Eats with fingers",
"2 = Cooperates when being fed", 
"1 = Takes food in mouth but won't swallow",
"0 = Doesn't open mouth when fed")
/ optionvalues = ("8", "7", "6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons Drinking>
/caption = "9. Drinking"
/ options = (
"5 = Drinks from a full cup alone",
"4 = Drinks alone from a half-full cup",
"3 = Drinks from a half-full cup but spills a great deal",
"2 = Cooperates when helped to drink", 
"1 = Takes liquid into mouth without swallowing",
"0 = Doesn't open mouth")
/ optionvalues = ("5", "4", "3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons UrinaryContinence>
/caption = "10. Urinary continence"
/ options = (
"8 = Independent, has no accidents",
"7 = Independent, never has accidents during the day",
"6 = Independent but has occasional accidents during the day",
"5 = No accidents but indicates need to be taken to toilet",
"4 = No accidents but needs to be taken regularly to toilet",
"3 = Occasional daytime accidents - lets caretaker know",
"2 = Occasional daytime accidents - doesn't let caretaker know", 
"1 = Frequent daytime accidents",
"0 = Completely incontinent")
/ optionvalues = ("8", "7", "6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons fecalContinence>
/caption = "11. fecal continence"
/ options = (
"7 = Independent, no accidents",
"6 = Independent, has no daytime accidents",
"5 = Independent but occasional accidents",
"4 = Indicates need to caretaker, no daytime accidents",
"3 = At least a weekly accident in the daytime, tell caretaker",
"2 = At least a weekly accident, doesn't tell caretaker", 
"1 = Accidents more than once a week",
"0 = Completely incontinent")
/ optionvalues = ("7", "6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<checkboxes UseofToilet>
/ caption="12. Independent use of toilet (score 1 if able)"
/ required = false
/ options=(
"Able to use a gesture or word to indicate need", 
"Doesn't use other inappropriate containers",
"Lowers clothing without help",
"Sits on seat without help",
"Uses toilet paper without being told",
"Pulls up clothes without being told",
"Washes hands without being told"
)
</checkboxes>

<radiobuttons Bathing>
/caption = "13. Bathing"
/ options = (
"6 = Washes and dries self without prompting",
"5 = Washes and dries self if asked",
"4 = Washes and dries self partially if asked",
"3 = Washes and dries self partially if helped",
"2 = Tries unsuccessfully to wash self", 
"1 = Cooperates when being bathed",
"0 = Doesn't cooperate when being bathed")
/ optionvalues = ("6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<checkboxes WashingHandsandFace>
/ caption="14. Washing hands and face (score 1 if able)"
/ required = false
/ options=(
"Turns on tap", 
"Washes hands with soap unaided",
"Rinses hands alone",
"Washes face with soap and face-washer",
"Dries hands",
"Dries face"
)
</checkboxes>

<radiobuttons DentalHygiene>
/caption = "15. Dental hygiene"
/ options = (
"4 = No teeth or dentures",
"4 = Brushes teeth or dentures alone",
"3 = Brushes teeth alone without toothpaste",
"2 = Brushes teeth with help", 
"1 = Cooperates when teeth brushed by caretaker",
"0 = Does not cooperate when teeth being brushed")
/ optionvalues = ("4", "4", "3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons Shaving>
/caption = "16. Shaving"
/ options = (
"5 = Does not need to shave",
"5 = Shaves alone without help",
"4 = Shves alone if told to",
"3 = Shaves alone if told how to",
"2 = Shaves with help", 
"1 = Cooperates when being shaved",
"0 = Doesn't cooperate when being shaved")
/ optionvalues = ("5", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<radiobuttons Walking>
/caption = "1. Walking"
/ options = (
"7 = Goes up and down stairs alone placing only one foot per step",
"6 = Goes up and down stairs with both feet on each step",
"5 = Walks alone but can't manage stairs",
"4 = Walks alone with aid of a wall or rail",
"3 = Walks with a stick",
"2 = Walks unaided with a walking-frame", 
"1 = Can walk with frame only if helped to feet",
"0 = Unable to walk alone")
/ optionvalues = ("7", "6", "5", "4", "3", "2", "1", "0")
/required = true
/orientation = vertical
</radiobuttons>

<checkboxes PostureAndGait>
/ caption="2. Posture and gait (score 1 if absent)"
/ required = false
/ options=(
"Drags feet", 
"Lowered head",
"Stomach protruding because of posture",
"Shoulders forward and back curved"
)
</checkboxes>

<checkboxes Handcontrol>
/ caption="3. Hand control (score 1 if able)"
/ required = false
/ options=(
"Able to gather up objects", 
"Can pull the lid off tins",
"Able to turn pages",
"Pours liquids into containers",
"Turns taps on and off",
"Uses light switches",
"Uses a key for opening and closing a lock"
)
</checkboxes>

*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************
	SURVEYPAGES
*******************************************************************************************************************
*******************************************************************************************************************

<surveypage bas1>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ subcaption = "Language
"
/questions = [1 = oralcomprehension, oralexpression]
</surveypage>

<surveypage bas2>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ subcaption = "Language
"
/questions = [1 = nonverbalexpression, recogwrittenlanguage]
</surveypage>

<surveypage bas3>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ subcaption = "Language
"
/questions = [1 = writingability]
</surveypage>

<surveypage bas4>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ subcaption = "Social Integration
"
/questions = [1 = cooperativeness, contactwithothers, fampersonawareness]
</surveypage>

<surveypage bas5>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ subcaption = "Social Integration
"
/questions = [1 = problem_daytime_behavior]
</surveypage>

<surveypage bas6>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ subcaption = "Social Integration
"
/questions = [1 = problem_nighttime_behavior]
</surveypage>

<surveypage bas7>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ subcaption = "Occupation and Orientation
"
/questions = [1 = activities]
</surveypage>

<surveypage bas8>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ subcaption = "Occupation and Orientation
"
/questions = [1 = tasks, orientation]
</surveypage>


<surveypage bas9>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ subcaption = "Physical Independence
"
/questions = [1 = dressing, undressing]
</surveypage>

<surveypage bas10>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ subcaption = "Physical Independence
"
/questions = [1 = puttingonshoes, takingoffshoes]
</surveypage>

<surveypage bas11>
/caption ="<%parameters.pageinstructions%>"
/ subcaption = "Physical Independence
"
/questions = [1 = goingtobed, sleep]
